    "Between 1928 and 1933 works by Joan Mir\u00f3, Andr\u00e9 Masson, Robert Delaunay, Piet Mondrian, and Jean Arp were added to his gallery, the first to enter a public collection in the U. S. Gallatin, however, ignored Expressionism, Futurism, and Dada, art styles with less formal theory attached to them.": [],
    "In 1936 Gallatin renamed his museum the \"Museum of Living Art\" with his purchase of Picasso's <em>Three Musicians</em> (1921).": [],
    "Gallatin ceased his French buying trips in 1938 with the declaration of hostilities with Germany.": [],
    "Instead, he focused on American art.": [],
    "The later abstract expressionists Arshile Gorky and Willem de Kooning attributed their early development to the Museum of Living Art.": [
