    "<a href=\"/sweeneyj\">James Johnson Sweeney</a>, later curator of the Museum of Modern Art, New York, praised Gallatin in 1931 for showing the widest range of cubism in America, which the fledging Museum of Modern Art, founded two years after Gallatin's museum by <a href=\"/barra\">Alfred H. Barr, Jr.</a>, would spend the next decade amassing a similar collection.": [],
    "Gallatin's space at NYU is today Grey Art Gallery and Study Center.": []
